---
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
import PageHero from '../../components/PageHero.astro';
import Section from '../../components/Section.astro';

import retailHero from '../../assets/retail-tobacco-field.jpg';
import cigarTestimonial from '../../assets/retail-cigar-testimonial.jpg';

/*
 * 1:1 reproduction of the live gsuair.com retail sector page: same headings,
 * same copy, same order — nothing added, nothing removed. That includes the
 * placeholder h1 and the "air travel" template filler under it, both kept at
 * the owner's request, and the copy's own spelling/spacing quirks.
 *
 * The Greg Zimmerman testimonial is an image on the live page, not body copy,
 * so it is rendered as the image it is (quote carried in the alt text).
 */
---

<Base
  title="Retail Sector"
  description="Mold and fungi in cigar humidors and tobacco seed beds. ActivePure® Technology reduces mold and fungi levels to keep your product fresher longer."
>
  <PageHero
    title="IDENTIFY WHY RETAIL NEEDS OUR PRODUCT"
    lead="We are a small business dedicated to providing you with the best air travel experience possible. From booking your flights to ensuring your comfort during the journey, we are here to take care of everything. Browse our website to learn more about our services and book your next trip with us today!"
    image={retailHero}
    imageAlt="Harvested tobacco leaves hung on bamboo racks to dry"
  />

  <Section tone="tint">
    <Image
      src={cigarTestimonial}
      alt="Germ Solutions USA testimonial: The Tobacco Company utilizes Germ Solutions USA -ActivePure Technology to safeguard my staff and clients from COVID Exposure as well as our Cigar investment within our humidors against the potential development of Mold and Fungus. Greg Zimmerman, PCA President."
      widths={[400, 700, 1050]}
      sizes="(min-width: 1024px) 36rem, 100vw"
      class="mx-auto w-full max-w-2xl rounded-2xl shadow-lg"
      loading="lazy"
    />
  </Section>

  <Section tone="brand" title="What are the Green-Blue Spots on my Cigars?">
    <div class="mt-6 max-w-3xl space-y-5 text-lg leading-relaxed text-brand-100">
      <p>
        If you find blue /green spots on your cigars that leave a stain when you brush them off, the spots are probably
        mold . Mold is a damaging fungus that results from storing cigars in too high humidity and will ruin. the taste
        of your cigars .
      </p>
      <p>
        Candida parapsilosis and Penicillium ascomycetous are two common fungal names provided by a cigar mold study
        performed by an Australian biotech laboratory. Feeding on natural sugars secreted from the tobacco leaves, cigar
        mold can appear in many colors - white, red, green, blue, or yellow
      </p>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Section tone="tint" title="Tobacco Indoor Seed Beds Mold/Fungi Exposure">
    <div class="mt-6 max-w-3xl space-y-5 text-lg leading-relaxed text-slate-700">
      <p>
        Your indoor garden is never more vulnerable than in the first few weeks after you plant. Whether you start with
        seeds or clones, the tender seedlings can suffer from overheating, underfeeding, and lethal fungi .
      </p>
      <p>
        A very common problem when attempting to grow plants from seeds started indoors is the appearance of fuzzy
        white, gray, or black mold that causes the freshly sprouted seedlings to decay and collapse at the soil level.
        Collectively, the conditions caused by these fungi are known as "damping-off" disease , and it is a death
        sentence for baby plants.
      </p>
      <p>
        Blue mold of tobacco is caused by Peronospora hyoscyami f.sp. Peronospora tabacina, is a fungus-like organism
        that is highly destructive to tobacco seed beds, transplants, and production fields in the humid farming zones of
        the southeastern and eastern United States, Canada, and countries bordering the Caribbean basin.
      </p>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Section tone="brand" title="Answer">
    <div class="mt-6 max-w-3xl space-y-5 text-lg leading-relaxed text-brand-100">
      <p>
        From the data of the study conducted at the Pittsburgh "Burn" Lounge between May 24th and June 6th 2022,
        ActivePure® Technology inactivated airborne Aspergillus/Penicillium mold to zero .
      </p>
      <p>
        ActivePure® Technology will greatly reduce the Mold and Fungi levels to safeguard Humidors and keep your product
        fresher longer. From a manufacturing standpoint we can safeguard your seedlings from the indoor grow space until
        they are ready to transplanted in the field.
      </p>
    </div>
  </Section>
</Base>
